1.  With the Protoflux Tool equipped, grab the "Seconds" slot
2.  Open your Context Menu and select "Unpack"
Note: in Desktop Mode, press "2" to equip the Development tool, and CTRL+T to open the Context Menu
3.  To remove the gizmos, swap tools and select "Deselect All" on your Context Menu, then swap back
4.  Grab a "Smooth Slerp" node and position it to the right of the "Axis Angle" node
5.  Pull out a connector from the "Input" input of the "Smooth Slerp" node and connect it to the output of the "Axis Angle" node
Note: in Desktop mode, press SHIFT+R after pulling out a connector to create a "float Input" node
6.  Pull out a connector from "Speed" input of the "Smooth Slerp" node and secondary click to create a "float Input" field
7.  Set the value of the field to "2"
8.  Connect the input of the "Value Field Drive (FloatQ)" node to the output of the "Smooth Slerp" node
9.  You will now notice that the second hand changes positions in a smoother fashion
Note: in Desktop mode, target any node and press and hold CTRL+R to select all of the nodes
10. Secondary click-and-hold on any of the nodes to select all of the nodes
11. Grab the "Seconds" slot, open your Context Menu, and select "Pack Into"
